Diameters range from 2-1/16" to 8", depending on configuration. Applications include agricultural and power transmission equipment, and conveyor systems. Generally used as tighteners or direction changers; available for all standard, flat and "V" belts. Permanently lubricated and sealed against grime and dirt. Fit into existing design with little or no engineering changes, or readily adapted to new designs.

Chain and Sprocket Idlers are compact units made for various chain types, including single and extended pitch roller chain, as well as detachable link chain. They are normally mounted on standard 1/2", 5/8" or 3/4" bolts, and include accurately contoured hardened teeth to resist wear and damage to the chain. Designs range from 6 to 18 teeth in various configurations. Typical applications include gathering chains on corn heads and other harvesting equipment, exercise machines, and packaging machines. Compact and easy to install. Built for long maintenance-free service life. Available in a range of a sprocket sizes and configurations which accommodate all conventional chain driven equipment. Precision Idlers are available in Flat Belt or V-belt styles with single or double row precision radial bearings riveted between soft steel flanges. They are used where loads and speeds are greater than required for unground bearings-usually over 2000 RPM. Many are used on modern combines. Flanged and V-belt idlers are available with single row bearings with a bore size to clear 1/2" and 5/8" bolts. Flanged and straight sided idlers for flat belts are available with double row bearings and bushed to clear 1/2", 5/8" and 3/4" bolts. Generally used as tighteners or direction changers; available for all standard, flat and "V" belts. Permanently lubricated and sealed against grime and dirt. Fit into existing design with little or no engineering changes or readily adapted to new designs. Basic Radial Load Rating of Precision Bearing is 1, 820 Pounds.

Rubber Tire Idlers are similar to flanged belt idlers except that they have a rubber tire captured between the flanges. Various tire diameters are available from 3 1/2" to 10". They are typically used in agricultural planters, belt conveyor systems, and as snowmobile bogey wheels. Same basic design and construction as other AG units except for the addition of a rubber tire or sprocket. Popular as snowmobile bogie wheels. Can be used as a non destructive belt tightener to reduce wear on soft material drive belts.

Adapter Bearings are a series of mounted ball bearing units designed for use in equipment where shafts are supported in frames or sheet metal surfaces. Typical applications include overhead doors, conveyor systems, packaging machines, and agricultural equipment. They provide a combination of features which literally give them universal adaptability; hence the name Adapter Bearing. In addition to its functional advantages the Aetna Adapter Bearing offers manufacturers important assembly line savings. Combining a self-aligning bearing. seals, a mounting flange, and shaft locking device in a single compact pro-lubricated installation, without further time consuming assembling or adjustment. A variety of mounting hole configurations are available. Eccentric shaft-locking collars are available for most sizes, as well as extended inner rings with set screws or drilled holes for pins. Combined self-aligning bearings, seals, mounting flange and locking collar in a single, compact pre-lubricated "package. " Ready for quick, easy mounting with standard bolts wherever shafts can be supported. Used to support shaft on overhead doors and gates in shopping malls. Extra heavy gauge steel flanges support higher loads required for large door application. Furnished without locking collar provision.

Precision Idlers are available in Flat Belt or V-belt styles with single or double row precision radial bearings riveted between soft steel flanges. They are used where loads and speeds are greater than required for unground bearings-usually over 2000 RPM. Many are used on modern combines. Flanged and V-belt idlers are available with single row bearings with a bore size to clear 1/2" and 5/8" bolts. Flanged and straight sided idlers for flat belts are available with double row bearings and bushed to clear 1/2", 5/8" and 3/4" bolts. Generally used as tighteners or direction changers; available for all standard, flat and "V" belts. Permanently lubricated and sealed against grime and dirt. Fit into existing design with little or no engineering changes or readily adapted to new designs. Basic Radial Load Rating of Precision Bearing is 3, 340 Pounds.

Rubber Tire Idlers are similar to flanged belt idlers except that they have a rubber tire captured between the flanges. Various tire diameters are available from 3 1/2" to 10". They are typically used in agricultural planters, belt conveyor systems, and as snowmobile bogey wheels. Same basic design and construction as other AG units except for the addition of a rubber tire or sprocket. Popular as snowmobile bogie wheels. Can be used as a non destructive belt tightener to reduce wear on soft material drive belts.

Chain and Sprocket Idlers are compact units made for various chain types, including single and extended pitch roller chain, as well as detachable link chain. They are normally mounted on standard 1/2", 5/8" or 3/4" bolts, and include accurately contoured hardened teeth to resist wear and damage to the chain. Designs range from 6 to 18 teeth in various configurations. Typical applications include gathering chains on corn heads and other harvesting equipment, exercise machines, and packaging machines. Compact and easy to install. Built for long maintenance-free service life. Available in a range of a sprocket sizes and configurations which accommodate all conventional chain driven equipment. Outer flanges are made of heavier gauge steel for greater life and load carrying ability.
